'''''Star Wars Insider'' 29''' is the twenty-ninth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in Spring [[1996]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Publisher"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with Rick McCallum" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[The Wonder Column|The New Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[Lucasfilm's Latest]]"
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Scoring the Trilogy]]" &ndash; ''Shadows of the Empire'' {{C|by [[Lukas Kendall]]}}
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &ndash; Creating the ''Shadows'' Comic Book {{C|by [[Bob Cooper]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"

===Features===
*"[[The Battle of Hoth (illustration)|The Battle of Hoth]]" {{C|illustration by [[Rebecca Guay]]}}
*:<small>This exclusive new illustration by Rebecca Guay shows the cold, bitter, final moments of this famous battle from ''The Empire Strikes Back''</small>
*"[[Brian Daley: 1947-1996]]" {{C|by [[James Luceno]]}}
*:<small>The beloved ''Star Wars'' scribe is remembered by one of his best friends, James Luceno.</small>
*"[[Into the Shadows: A Profile of Author Steve Perry]]" {{C|by [[Kevin Fitzpatrick]]}}
*:<small>Kevin Fitzpatrick finds out what it's like to put words in Vader's mouth.</small>
*"[[On-location: Tatooine]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>Jon Bradley Snyder reports on [[Rick McCallum]] and [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]] search for prequel location sites.</small>
*"[[The Unsung Collectible: Star Wars Magazines|The Unsung Collectibles: ''Star Wars'' Magazines]]" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*:<small>Jon Bradley Snyder looks at some of the greatest ''Star Wars'' magazine covers.</small>
*"[[Star Wars 101: College Instructors Bring Star Wars into the Classroom|''Star Wars'' 101: College Instructors Bring ''Star Wars'' into the Classroom]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*:<small>Jamie Painter talks ''Star Wars'' 101 with four different college professors.</small>

